      <p class="lead text-xl text-gray-600">
        Tokyo transforms after dark into a photographer's paradise of neon lights, reflective surfaces, and urban energy.
      </p>
      
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Prime Photo Locations</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-16">
      {photoSpots.map(spot => (
        <PhotoSpot {...spot} />
      ))}
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Photography Tips</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-16">
      {photographyTips.map(tip => (
        <PhotoTip {...tip} />
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2>Essential Information</h2>
      <h3>Best Times to Visit</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Blue hour (just after sunset)</li>
        <li>Rainy evenings for reflections</li>
        <li>Weekend nights for peak activity</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Equipment Recommendations</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Fast prime lenses (f/1.4 or f/1.8)</li>
        <li>Sturdy tripod for long exposures</li>
        <li>Weather-sealed camera body</li>
        <li>Microfiber cloths for lens care</li>
      </ul>

      <blockquote>
        <p>"Tokyo at night is a symphony of light and shadow, waiting to be captured."</p>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>